25|$|In Norse society, a vǫlva was {{an elderly}} woman who had {{released}} herself from the strong family bonds that normally surrounded women in Norse clans. She travelled the land, usually followed by a retinue of young people, and she was summoned <b>in</b> <b>times</b> <b>of</b> <b>crisis.</b> She had immense authority and she charged well for her services.|$|E
