25|$|The pagan sacrifices, {{known as}} blót, were {{seasonal}} celebrations where gifts were offered to appropriate gods and {{attempts were made}} to forecast what the coming season would be like. Similar events were sometimes convened <b>in</b> <b>times</b> <b>of</b> <b>crisis,</b> for much the same reasons. The sacrifices, consisting of gold, weapons, animals, and even human beings, were hung on the branches of a holy tree.|$|E
